db.juhaku.juhakudb.filter

Class QueryProcessor.Alias

  • java.lang.Object
    • db.juhaku.juhakudb.filter.QueryProcessor.Alias
  • Enclosing class:
    QueryProcessor

    public static class QueryProcessor.Alias
extends java.lang.Object
    Alias provides centralized way of aliasing sql queries to database tables. It can be used to create alias for entities of database or joins created with filters.

    All sql queries are aliased via this class to maintain integrity inside queries.

    Since:
    1.2.0

    • Method Detail

      • forJoin

        public static java.lang.String forJoin(Root.Join join)
        Get alias for join. If custom alias is used then it will be returned otherwise alias is first looked from cache. If cached alias is not found new will be generated and set to cache for later usage.
        Parameters:
        join - Instance of Root.Join to get alias for.
        Returns:
        String value of alias for join.
        Since:
        1.2.0

      • forModel

        public static java.lang.String forModel(java.lang.Class<?> model)
        Get alias for model class. Model class must be a database entity. Alias is first looked from cache. If cached alias is not found new will be generated and set to cache for later usage.
        Parameters:
        model - Instance of Class of entity to get alias for.
        Returns:
        String value of alias for entity.
        Since:
        1.2.0
